Merge pull request #266 from jflinter/master

Fix minimum deployment target for iOS framework

Fixed memory leak in POPCGUtils

Previously a -[NSColor CGColor] and a +[NSColor colorWithCGColor:] shim
were added unconditionally for OS X even though those methods exist
"natively" since 10.8.
Furthermore the CGColor property shim returned a retained CGColorRef
instead of returning a non retained ("internal pointer") one. This lead
to a memory leak, which can be fixed by storing the reference as an
associated property on the NSColor instance.
Both methods are now correctly implemented and used in
POPCGColorGetRGBAComponents() and POPNSColorRGBACreate() respectively,
without overwriting globally visible methods.
fix minimum deployment target for iOS framework

Cancelling any ongoing animation in UIScrollView

If there is any UIScrollView animation of any sort:
- Say the user scrolled a little bit and the UIScrollView is decelerating. 
- Or `[scrollView setContentOffSet:p animated:YES]` was triggered.
- Or the user tapped on the statusbar to scroll to top

These animations will interfere with pop-animation since they will both work simultaneously. Setting `-[UIScrollView setContentOffset:animated:]` will cancel/stop any UIScrollView animation.
